title: 820-00281: No booting up but CPU/GPU warm with fan spinning.
message:
I have this board, customer said it wasn't getting image to the display but did get image on external display. Once i started working on it, i noticed there was no usb-c activity on any of the port, which also meant no external display image. Started probing and noticed L7410 and L7421 (PPVCCGT_S0_CPU) were reading 0v. 

Signals to U7410/U7420
PP5V_S0 - 5v
PPBUS_HS_CPU - 12.6
CPUGT_FCCM - 0.015
CPUGT_PWM1 - 2.57
CPUGT_PWM2 - 2.58

current pull by the board swings inconsistently between 1.20 and .91A

Any suggestions?

title: 820-00281: No booting up but CPU/GPU warm with fan spinning.
message:
VCCGT refers to iGPU and doesn't come on when board boots.

USB-C ports switch to 20V?
3V3_G3H and PPBUS_G3H present?

title: 820-00281: No booting up but CPU/GPU warm with fan spinning.
message:
Looks like board doesn't really boot.
PPVCC_S0_CPU should change in few steps, untill 0.6V aprox.
Possibly bad CPU.
Try known good BIOS, just in case.

title: 820-00281: No booting up but CPU/GPU warm with fan spinning.
message: Tried good bios with same issue, and PPVCC_SO_CPU never steps down.
